'''Domkach''' is a folk dance of [[Indian states]] of [[Bihar]] and [[Jharkhand]]. In Bihar, Domkach dance is performed in [[Mithila (region)|Mithila]] and [[Bhojpuri region|Bhojpur]] regions.<ref>http://folklibrary.com/index.php/folkform/?id=211-domkach&catid=210&parent=&child=Domkach&color=</ref> In Jharkhand, it is performed in the [[Chota Nagpur Plateau]] region by [[Nagpuri people]]. The women of bridegroom's family  perform this dance during marriage. They dance in circle and lyrics of the song are satrical.<ref>http://ezccindia.org/jharkhand.html</ref>

