'''Kechagiadikos''' is a circular dance done on the Island of [[Lemnos]] in Greece. The dance is done free hold and moves in a circle. Both men and women dance the dance to the song 'Βρε Κεχαγιά Περήφανε' "Vre Kehagia Perifane'. The word Kehagia (Κεχαγιάς) comes from the Turkish word ''Kahya'', housekeeper.{{cn|date=April 2015}}

