A [[lottery]] exists within the '''United States Virgin Islands''', the only US lottery outside the mainland and [[Puerto Rico]]. It was established in 1937 and became an independent agency of the territorial government in 1971.[https://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/pkg/GPO-DOI-IGREPORTS-01-i-290/html/GPO-DOI-IGREPORTS-01-i-290.htm] The USVI is a member of the [[Multi-State Lottery Association]] (MUSL). It is the smallest US lottery to offer either [[Powerball]], [[Mega Millions]] or [[scratchcard]] games. The USVI Lottery is also a member of the [[Caribbean Lottery]], in which other islands, such as [[Sint Maarten]], [[Saint Kitts and Nevis]], and [[Barbados]], participate. Minimum age to play the Virgin Islands Lottery is 18.

The lottery headquarters is in [[Charlotte Amalie, United States Virgin Islands|Charlotte Amalie]] on [[Saint Thomas, U.S. Virgin Islands|St. Thomas]].

