{{Infobox person | name = Zuzana Fialová | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1974|05|17|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Bratislava]], [[Czechoslovak Socialist Republic|Czechoslovakia]] | death_date = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | death_cause = | other_names = | occupation = [[actress]], director | years_active = 1989–present | employer = [[Slovak National Theatre|SND]], Bratislava (2003<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theatre.sk/sk/download/Publikacie/Rocenky/2002-2003.pdf|title=Slovak Theatrical Season 2002/2003|work=The Theatre Institute|publisher=Divadelný ústav|accessdate=2011-09-08|page=12|language=sk}}</ref>–2010) | organization = [[Academy of Performing Arts in Bratislava|VŠMU, Bratislava]] | spouse = | partner = | children = David Matulík (1997) | parents = | relatives = | callsign = | awards = | signature = | signature_alt = | website = [http://www.snd.sk/?detail-1&meno=fialova-zuzana Slovak National Theatre] }}
'''Zuzana Fialová''' (born 17 May 1974 in [[Bratislava]], [[Czechoslovak Socialist Republic|ČSSR]]) is a [[Slovakia|Slovak]] [[actress]].<ref name="osobnosti">{{cite web|url=http://www.osobnosti.sk/index.php?os=zivotopis&ID=59191|title=Zuzana Fialová|publisher=osobnosti.sk|language=Slovak|accessdate=24 January 2011}}</ref>
She attended the music and drama department at the Conservatory in Bratislava, and in 1998 graduated acting studies at the drama faculty of the [[Academy of Performing Arts in Bratislava]]. Currently she is preparing for a graduate degree. She is divorced and has a son.
In 2006, she won the first season of the Slovak version of ''[[Dancing with the Stars]]'' entitled ''[[Let's Dance (Slovak TV series)|Let's Dance]]''.
In January 2011, Fialová was among those injured in the [[2011 Domodedovo International Airport bombing|Domodedovo International Airport bombing]].<ref name="Domodedovo">{{cite news |title=Slovak actress Fialová remains in a Russian hospital after bomb blast |url=http://spectator.sme.sk/articles/view/41444/10/slovak_actress_fialova_remains_in_a_russian_hospital_after_bomb_blast.html |work=[[The Slovak Spectator]] |date=January 25, 2011 |first=Michaela |last=Terenzani}}</ref>
